# Line-ending policy for the dms-dashboard repo.
# Rationale: the repo is almost entirely web assets (HTML/CSS/JS/SVG) served
# as-is. LF everywhere keeps diffs stable regardless of contributor OS or
# editor, and avoids the "5,048 lines changed" noise commits that happen
# when an editor on Windows re-saves with CRLF.
#
# * text=auto   -> detect text files; binary files untouched
# eol=lf        -> store LF in the repo AND check out LF in the working tree
#
# See: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary markers (belt-and-suspenders; `text=auto` would usually
# detect these, but being explicit prevents edge-case misdetection).
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.webp   binary
*.ico    binary
*.pdf    binary
*.zip    binary
*.woff   binary
*.woff2  binary
*.ttf    binary
*.otf    binary
*.eot    binary
